other_tests.findings: Functional C1 esterase inhibitor level of 27% (normal level is more than 30%)

other_tests.procedure_name: Intravenous Contrast Material–Enhanced CT of the Abdomen and Pelvis
other_tests.findings: Diffuse circumferential thickening of the gastric antrum and all segments of the duodenum with marked 1.0–1.5-cm thickening and low attenuation in the submucosa, compatible with edema, and dilated loops of proximal jejunum.
other_tests.changes_over_time: Increased and more extensive edematous thickening of the small bowel and gastric antrum compared to prior CT images taken in January and March 2005.
